9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line></svg></div></div></figure></div><p>如果我是新加坡政府，我的目标是赚更多这样的街道。如果他们有能力用零虫子修剪整齐的绿色植物来覆盖这座城市，那么他们有能力使街道对行人群众更愉快。</p><p>无论如何，撇开散文，如果没有，您绝对应该在某个时候访问新加坡。美妙的财富和未来派的太阳朋克建筑只是其中的两个景点 - 还有令人惊叹的食物，有趣的民族社区，可爱的景色，有趣的历史以及相当壮观的建筑风格。</p><p>只需记住不要意外带任何大麻，否则他们会<a href="https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/up-to-30-years-jail-for-possession-of-cannabis-with-roll-out-of-stricter-drug-laws-from-june">用拐杖殴打您，并将您送进监狱数十年</a>。 </p><div><hr></div><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Subscribe now&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"><a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/subscribe?"><span>现在订阅</span></a></p><p class="button-wrapper" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share&quot;,&quot;text&quot;:&quot;Share&quot;,&quot;action&quot;:null,&quot;class&quot;:null}" data-component-name="ButtonCreateButton"> <a class="button primary" href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/singapore-urbanism?utm_source=substack&utm_medium=email&utm_content=share&action=share"><span>分享</span></a></p>; 
Yes, it's possible to imagine progressive dystopias We shouldn't just worry about the means of progress, but the ends as well. https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressive https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressiveNoah Smith Fri, 10 Nov 2023 07:52:40 GMT <div class="captioned-image-container"><figure> <a class="image-link is-viewable-img image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg" width="722" height="481.3333333333333" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/c8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:624,&quot;width&quot;:936,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:722,&quot;bytes&quot;:135733,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false,&quot;topImage&quot;:true,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Fc8d5d1ea-296e-471c-9aff-fcd212ef244c_936x624.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" fetchpriority="high"></picture></div></a> <polyline points="15 3 21 3 21 9"></polyline><polyline points="9 21 3 21 3 15"></polyline><line x1="21" x2="14" y1="3" y2="10"></line><line x1="3" x2="10" y1="21" y2="14"></line><figcaption class="image-caption"> “<a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00/14486751845">唯一可持续的增长是去增长</a>”， <a href="https://www.flickr.com/photos/53301297@N00">pasa47</a> ， <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.0/?ref=openverse">CC BY 2.0</a></figcaption></figure></div><p>最近有一个想法一直困扰着我。几个月前，布拉德·德隆和我<a href="https://braddelong.substack.com/p/podcast-hexapodia-liii-rule-1-no#details">做了一个播客</a>，我们讨论了布丽安娜·吴、马特·伊格莱西亚斯和埃兹拉·克莱因等中左派人士对一些左派人士的反击。布拉德将这些阻力归结为从根本上讲是<em>策略</em>问题——在他看来，布里安娜、马特和埃兹拉对一些进步人士在试图实现乌托邦时使用的手段感到沮丧，并主张采取更务实、更有效的方法。这是一个长期传统的一部分，倡导社会变革的积极分子争论社会已经准备好进行多大程度的变革。</p><p>但是，尽管我确实认为有些事情正在进行，但我不同意布拉德（Brad），这主要是倒退的目的。取而代之的是，我认为我们真正看到的是对进步主义者似乎正在为之奋斗的某些<em>目标</em>越来越不适，而不是关于变革的步伐，而是关于它的方向。当布拉德要求我列出一些反乌托邦进步愿景的例子时，我立即说“去生长”，他同意了。</p><p>不管怎样，请注意我说的是“一些”这个词。许多进步的愿景，比如更大的经济平等、缩小种族贫富差距以及扭转气候变化，都是我想要的！如果你将这篇文章解读为说进步主义<em>大体上</em>是一个反乌托邦项目，那么你就严重误解了我。我也不是说保守主义比进步主义更好，或者说政治右翼不包含自己的反乌托邦愿景。确实如此。</p><p>取而代之的是，我要说的是，在2010年代令人震惊的匆忙中所接受的一些大想法被误导了，应该被丢弃，以便为人类实际上想要生活的乌托邦努力。</p><p>这里列出了四个这样的愿景。</p><h4>退生长</h4><p>当然，这是对布拉德问题的简单回答。我已经写了多篇文章，详细论证了为什么停止或逆转经济增长（这一想法在过去十年中在一些进步人士中变得流行）作为限制人类环境影响的一种方式既不可行，也不受欢迎。首先，我认为去增长所需的生活水平下降使其在政治上成为不可能的事情，并且所涉及的全球中央计划的数量将无法实施： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;52bf6b2d-b886-46cf-8a98-7325f073a207&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;I was going to write a lengthy post explaining why &#8220;degrowth&#8221; &#8212; the idea that we need to halt economic growth in order to save the planet &#8212; is a very bad idea. But in the meantime, other people have written that post, or recorded that podcast, and done it well. These include&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2021-09-06T08:40:54.095Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2Faeddab2a-6c56-4e5b-9c35-9ca0fecd86bd_1024x682.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/people-are-realizing-that-degrowth&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:39760555,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:129,&quot;comment_count&quot;:106,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:false}"></div><p>我还认为，解决气候变化需要增长，因为用太阳能、风能和电池取代我们的能源需要<em>大量</em>的经济产出。一旦我们转向这些能源，它们就会变得非常便宜（由于学习曲线），我们实际上会比以前持续更高的消耗。</p><p>在后续文章中，我批评了去增长想法背后的研究和言论，这些想法通常基于意识形态驱动的伪科学： </p><div class="digest-post-embed" data-attrs="{&quot;nodeId&quot;:&quot;15f58e2c-0355-411d-a35f-7e2969e03f23&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;A year and a half ago, I wrote a post entitled &#8220;People are realizing that degrowth is bad&#8221;. Around that time, the degrowth movement had started to receive a bit of attention in the U.S., as part of the general push for major action on climate change. But writers like&quot;,&quot;size&quot;:&quot;sm&quot;,&quot;isEditorNode&quot;:true,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;Degrowth: We can't let it happen here!&quot;,&quot;publishedBylines&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:8243895,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Noah Smith&quot;,&quot;bio&quot;:&quot;Econ blogger&quot;,&quot;photo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/89fd964a-586f-461a-9f5a-ea4587d45728_397x441.png&quot;,&quot;is_guest&quot;:false,&quot;bestseller_tier&quot;:10000}],&quot;post_date&quot;:&quot;2023-05-24T01:54:00.942Z&quot;,&quot;cover_image&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F058020be-b262-4c24-88c2-ba3e1c8e0184_1024x681.jpeg&quot;,&quot;cover_image_alt&quot;:null,&quot;canonical_url&quot;:&quot;https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/degrowth-we-cant-let-it-happen-here&quot;,&quot;section_name&quot;:null,&quot;id&quot;:123140587,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;newsletter&quot;,&quot;reaction_count&quot;:201,&quot;comment_count&quot;:80,&quot;publication_name&quot;:&quot;Noahpinion&quot;,&quot;publication_logo_url&quot;:&quot;https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fbucketeer-e05bbc84-baa3-437e-9518-adb32be77984.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F04281755-2cd6-42e5-a496-e69153abebb2_281x281.png&quot;,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"></div><p>正如我在第二篇文章中所解释的那样，我将脱生物视为试图使民族衰落的尝试，这就是为什么这个想法在欧洲比美国更受欢迎的原因</p><p>我不想彻底解决这一点，但我认为有必要强调去增长的未来将是多么令人不快和不人道。富裕国家的人民将被迫接受低得多的生活水平，而发展中国家的人民将面临<a href="https://brankomilanovic.substack.com/p/degrowth-solving-the-impasse-by-magical">更加渺茫的未来</a>。这种情况无疑会引起不满，导致对强制实现大规模贫困的领导人的强烈抵制。在推翻去增长政权之后，我们会看到钟摆完全转向承诺无限资源消耗的领导人，此时环境将比以前更糟。除此之外，经济衰退将使投资绿色能源和其他保护环境的技术变得更加困难。</p><p>因此，尽管我认为我们确实需要担心增长的潜在负面后果并尽力减轻这些危害，但我认为试图使自己贫穷以拯救环境会成为我们和环境的灾难性错误。这不是任何进步人士应该为之奋斗的事情。</p><h4>驱逐“殖民者”</h4><p>非殖民化，正如我们通常使用的词——即国家从欧洲帝国霸主手中获得独立——在我出生时实际上已经完成。这对世界来说是一件非常好的事情，无论是在道德上还是<a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/against-hickelism">在经济上</a>。但近年来，美国的一些进步人士开始谈论一种完全不同类型的“非殖民化”——将“殖民者”人口驱逐出其祖先定居的地区。</p><p> “非殖民化”的另一种含义一直在人文学术界和一些左倾的媒体和激进主义运动中越来越受欢迎，但在哈马斯于10月7日对以色列袭击以色列之后，它爆炸到了国家舞台上。在哈马斯的屠杀和强奸狂欢发生后，《Teen Vogue》杂志的作家 Najma Sharif 发布了以下推文： </p><div class="captioned-image-container"><figure><a class="image-link image2" target="_blank" href="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg" data-component-name="Image2ToDOM"><div class="image2-inset"><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw"><img src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg" width="527" height="188.31466666666665" data-attrs="{&quot;src&quot;:&quot;https://substack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com/public/images/1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg&quot;,&quot;srcNoWatermark&quot;:null,&quot;fullscreen&quot;:null,&quot;imageSize&quot;:null,&quot;height&quot;:134,&quot;width&quot;:375,&quot;resizeWidth&quot;:527,&quot;bytes&quot;:19741,&quot;alt&quot;:null,&quot;title&quot;:null,&quot;type&quot;:&quot;image/jpeg&quot;,&quot;href&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true,&quot;topImage&quot;:false,&quot;internalRedirect&quot;:null}" class="sizing-normal" alt="" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_424,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 424w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_848,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 848w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1272,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 1272w, https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_1456,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fsubstack-post-media.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fpublic%2Fimages%2F1be80b0a-b5a2-4898-a77d-4fd80df00a22_375x134.jpeg 1456w" sizes="100vw" loading="lazy"></picture><div></div></div></figure></div><p>几天后，斯坦福大学的一位讲师在旨在解释和捍卫哈马斯袭击的课堂练习中将<a href="https://www.thedailybeast.com/stanford-lecturer-suspended-after-allegedly-calling-israel-a-colonizer-in-class">犹太学生列为</a>“殖民者”：</p><blockquote><p>斯坦福大学的一名讲师已被停职，因为学校正在调查他在两堂课上根据学生的“身份和背景”针对学生的指控，他在两堂课上就<a href="https://www.thedailybeast.com/keyword/israel">以色列</a>与<a href="https://www.thedailybeast.com/keyword/hamas">哈马斯</a>冲突进行了即兴演讲。在其中一个课程中，讲师首先将战争归咎于犹太复国主义者，然后要求“犹太学生举手”，犹太学生领袖努里亚·科恩（Nourya Cohen）告诉《<em>旧金山纪事报》</em> 。 “他问有多少犹太人在大屠杀中丧生，”科恩说，并补充说，当有人回答六百万时，“他说，‘是的。只有六百万。”一位自称在课堂上与三名学生交谈过的拉比告诉犹太新闻媒体<a href="https://forward.com/news/564587/stanford-university-jewish-students-instructor-hamas/">《前进》</a> ，讲师继续说道，“殖民者杀害了超过六百万人。以色列是一个殖民者。”科恩和另一位学生领袖声称，老师随后在班上四处将学生划分为“殖民者”或“被殖民者”，具体取决于他们所说的来自哪里。</p></blockquote><p><a href="https://www.noahpinion.blog/p/yes-its-possible-to-imagine-progressive">阅读更多</a></p>;
